The USA changes the rules for obtaining a visa
Before their conference at the consulate, the people must present themselves to the service offices for visa applications; costs will be reduced.
From the 10th The procedures for applying for a visa in the United States embassy and consulates will change on January 1st of 2011.
In the new procedure, most applicants must introduce themselves to the visa application services (ASC, the initial letter in English) before their conference at the consulate.
The staff of the ASC takes up the biometric data of the applicant, which are checked by the consulate before the interview.
The new procedure has certain advantages for the aspirants, including:
The total costs for the processing of the visa decrease, because it is no longer necessary to pay the appointment, the processing of the visa application and the transport service with which the document is handed over separately.
The applicant makes only one payment covering the three services.
The current price remains unchanged: the representative to 140 dollars for a tourist visa, 150 dollars for visas with application (including visas for temporary workers) and 390 dollars for hands and investors.
Those who only want to extend their visa do not have to talk in the consulate, they only have to introduce themselves to the nearest ASC where they present their documents and their fingerprints are taken.
Since the biometric data is obtained in the ASC, applicants who need a second appointment for the conversation in the consulate remain there less time than before.
Those who apply for a visa at the consulates of Ciudad Juárez, Monterrey and Nuevo Laredo no longer have to pay the service premium of 26 dollars.
Additional information about the new visa application procedure can be found in the following website: http://mexico.usembassy.gov/boletines/sp101201-Visas-FAQs.html
